To create a footnote for the authors list in LaTeX, you can use the \footnote{} command. Here's an example of how you can do it:

\documentclass{article}

\begin{document}

\title{My Article}
\author{John Doe\footnote{Corresponding author} \and Jane Smith}

\maketitle

\section{Introduction}

In this section, we will discuss...

\end{document}

In this example, the \footnote{} command is used to create a footnote for the author's name "John Doe". The text inside the curly braces after \footnote{} is the content of the footnote. In this case, "Corresponding author" is added as the content of the footnote.

You can add more authors to the \author{} command by separating them with the \and command. For example, in the above code, "Jane Smith" is added as the second author.
